          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Overall experience with the school is very good so far. My son has been studying in the Pre-Primary section of GIIS Balewadi school since two years. The teachers of the GMP section are very supportive and caring .\n\nWe have seen lot of positive changes in my kid and we are very happy with the school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Banyan Tree International School - Mahalunge"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Amitesh Kumar"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-02-16",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I have been witnessing the journey of GIIS Balewadi School since its inception. In the last couple of years there have been many positive changes. The changes are really very good and keeping up with the changing needs of the world. Very happy with the cooperative attitude of the teachers for making my child more confident.\nRecently GMP annual day held in the campus. It was my first amazing experience to see my kids performing on stage at this early age with immense confidence and enthusiasm. I would like to thank GIIS School from bottom of my heart to give these kids such a beautiful platform to hone their talent and confidence.\nMy special thanks to Pinki Kumari ma’am for all the extra time and effort she put in to help my child grow and learn.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Banyan Tree International School - Mahalunge"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Ashish Toshniwal"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-02-10",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Our overall experience with this school is good. Though there were some admin issues initially but academics were never compromised. The staff and infra of this school is great especially when it comes to lower grade as my child is in grade 2. There are lot of competitive activities happening throughout the year which gives a great exposure to students. Also they have a clear focus on extra curricular activities apart from academics which ensures overall development of students. My child is close to completing her 1st year in this school on a very positive note. And last but not the least their grand annual event has already won the hearts of all the parents across all the grades. Thanks to the entire staff for their hard work during the entire year to make it a smooth ride by the end of the year.\n\nHope to see lot of positive things happening in next year as promised by Principal sir in the annual event.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Banyan Tree International School - Mahalunge"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Vivek Bansod"
          },
          "datePublished": "2022-10-10",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Overall, good school when it comes to an academics as well as extracurricular activities. My son got lot of exposure to different competition and learning experience where child can interact with students from other locations(within and outside of India)\nThe teachers are experts in their field and very cooperative. You can easily track your child’s progress through the various parent-teacher meetings. The meetings help you to interact with the teachers and clear all your doubts. I actually reserved 1 star for improvement like management, outer infra etc. otherwise it's great school. Happy to be part of GIIS Balewadi.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
      ]
